%h3= t('titles.developer', brand: t('titles.brand'))

- if admin_signed_in?
  %p
    Welcome back, #{@user.name}! #{link_to t('links.register_a_new_application'), new_api_application_path} or #{link_to t('links.view'), api_applications_path} your existing ones.
- else
  %p
    Welcome to the #{t('titles.brand')} developer portal!
  %p
    This particular instance of the Ohana API exposes information about various human services providers in #{t('admin.api_location')}.
  %p
    We'd love for you to build something that will connect underprivileged residents with the help they need (food, shelter, medical care, etc.).
  %p
    Read the #{link_to 'documentation', 'http://codeforamerica.github.io/ohana-api-docs/'} to learn more.
    If you're a Ruby developer, we encourage you to use the official #{link_to 'Ohanakapa', 'https://github.com/codeforamerica/ohanakapa-ruby'} Ruby library.
  %p
    #{link_to t('navigation.sign_up'), new_admin_registration_path} for a developer account, or #{link_to t('navigation.sign_in'), new_admin_session_path}.
